.TH HNS_SET_SERVERS_CSV 3 "30 June 2010"
.SH NAME
hns_set_servers_csv, hns_set_servers_ports_csv \- Set list of DNS servers to be used.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <hns.h>
.PP
.B int hns_set_servers_csv(hns_channel \fIchannel\fP, const char* \fIservers\fP)
.B int hns_set_servers_ports_csv(hns_channel \fIchannel\fP, const char* \fIservers\fP)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBhns_set_servers_csv\fP and \fBhns_set_servers_ports_csv\fPfunctions set
the list of DNS servers that HNS will query.  The format of the servers option is:

host[:port][,host[:port]]...

For example:

192.168.1.100,192.168.1.101,3.4.5.6
.PP
The \fBhns_set_servers_csv\fP function will ignore any port values specified in
the input string, whereare the \fBhns_set_servers_ports_csv\fP function will
apply any specified port values as the UDP and TCP port to be used for that
particular nameserver.

.SH RETURN VALUES
.B hns_set_servers_csv(3)
This function may return any of the following values:
.TP 15
.B HNS_SUCCESS
The name servers configuration was successfully initialized.
.TP 15
.B HNS_ENOMEM
The process's available memory was exhausted.
.TP 15
.B HNS_ENODATA
The channel data identified by
.IR channel
was invalid.
.TP 15
.B HNS_ENOTINITIALIZED
hns library initialization not yet performed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hns_set_servers (3)
.SH AVAILABILITY
\fBhns_set_servers_csv\fP was added in hns 1.7.2;
\fBhns_set_servers_ports_csv\fP was added in hns 1.11.0.
